{"type":"message","id":"f8f88564","parentId":"326df55b","timestamp":"2026-03-18T01:22:05.239Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-32421e6882af4e34bdc7293a1ed4ccd4","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 70,\n      \"score\": 0.7810256958007812,\n      \"snippet\": \"---\\nid: qb2-life-acceleration\\ntitle: \\\"Game of Life Scaling Demo\\\"\\ndescription: >-\\n  Conway's Game of Life at scale. Five progressive demos from 128×128 to 4096×4096 grids (16M cells), demonstrating parallel computation and performance scaling on Tenstorrent hardware.\\ncategory: qb2-demos\\ntags:\\n  - demo\\n  - qb2\\n  - game-of-life\\n  - performance\\n  - visualization\\n  - cellular-automata\\nsupportedHardware:\\n  - n150\\n  - n300\\n  - t3k\\n  - p100\\n  - p150\\n  - p300c\\n  - galaxy\\nstatus: validated\\nvalidatedOn:\\n  - p300c\\n  - n150\\nestimatedMinutes: 10\\n---\\n\\n# Game of Life Scaling Demo\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nFive progressive Conway's Game of Life demonstrations showing performance scaling:\\n\\n```\\nDemo 1: 128×128 grid      (\\n\\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md#L1-L70\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md#L1-L70\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cookbook-game-of-life.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 399,\n      \"endLine\": 472,\n      \"score\": 0.704022827744484,\n      \"snippet\": \"\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 8))\\n\\n    if title:\\n        ax.set_title(title)\\n    else:\\n        ax.set_title(f\\\"Generation {generation_num}\\\")\\n\\n    ax.imshow(grid, cmap='binary', interpolation='nearest')\\n    ax.axis('off')\\n    plt.tight_layout()\\n    plt.show()\\n\\ndef compare_patterns(patterns_dict):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Display multiple patterns side-by-side.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        patterns_dict: {name: grid} dictionary\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    n = len(patterns_dict)\\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, n, figsize=(4*n, 4))\\n\\n    if n == 1:\\n        axes = [axes]\\n\\n    for ax, (name, grid) in zip(axes, patterns_dict.items()):\\n        ax.set_title(name)\\n        ax.imshow(grid, cmap='binary', interpolation='nearest\\n\\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cookbook-game-of-life.md#L399-L472\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cookbook-game-of-life.md#L399-L472\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cs-fundamentals-02-memory.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 177,\n      \"endLine\": 226,\n      \"score\": 0.5653255119919777,\n      \"snippet\": \"│\\n\\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cs-fundamentals-02-memory.md#L177-L226\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cs-fundamentals-02-memory.md#L177-L226\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-agentic-inference.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 305,\n      \"endLine\": 372,\n      \"score\": 0.5358105570077896,\n      \"snippet\": \"3. Shows vLLM command for your configuration\\n4. Tests connection if server running\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 📊 Running the Demo\\n\\n### Quick Start (Mock)\\n\\n```bash\\ncd ~/tt-scratchpad/qb2-demos/agentic-inference\\n\\n# Super Demo with mock (no hardware)\\n./run_demo.sh 5\\n```\\n\\n### With vLLM (Hardware)\\n\\n```bash\\n# Ensure vLLM running (see setup above)\\n./run_demo.sh 5 --llm vllm\\n```\\n\\n### Custom Questions\\n\\n```bash\\n./run_demo.sh 5 --question \\\"How do transformers enable language understanding?\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### Advanced Options\\n\\n```bash\\n# Different model\\n./run_demo.sh 5 --llm vllm --model ~/models/Qwen3-8B\\n\\n# Remote vLLM server\\n./run_demo.sh 5 --llm vllm --vllm-url http://192.168.1.100:8000/v1\\n\\n# OpenAI for testing\\nexport OPENAI_AP\\n\\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-agentic-inference.md#L305-L372\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-agentic-inference.md#L305-L372\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 433,\n      \"endLine\": 518,\n      \"score\": 0.5358105570077896,\n      \"snippet\": \"help='Interactive menu to choose demo')\\n\\n    args = parser.parse_args()\\n\\n    if args.interactive:\\n        print(\\\"\\\\n🎪 LIFE ACCELERATION DEMO MENU 🎪\\\\n\\\")\\n        for num, spec in LifeAccelerator.DEMO_SPECS.items():\\n            print(f\\\"  [{num}] {spec['name']}\\\")\\n            print(f\\\"      Grid: {spec['grid_size'][0]}×{spec['grid_size'][1]}\\\")\\n            print()\\n\\n        choice = int(input(\\\"Choose demo (1-5): \\\"))\\n        args.demo = choice\\n\\n    # Initialize device\\n    device = ttnn.open_device(device_id=0)\\n\\n    try:\\n        # Run selected demo\\n        accelerator = LifeAccelerator(device, args.demo)\\n        accelerator.run()\\n    finally:\\n        ttnn.close_device(device)\\n\\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md#L433-L518\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md#L433-L518\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/tt-xla-jax.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 159,\n      \"endLine\": 233,\n      \"score\": 0.5358105570077896,\n      \"snippet\": \"pip install pjrt-plugin-tt --pre --upgrade --extra-index-url https://pypi.eng.aws.tenstorrent.com/\\n```\\n\\n**Flags explained:**\\n- `--pre`: Install pre-release (latest features, most tested)\\n- `--upgrade`: Ensure latest version\\n- `--extra-index-url`: Tenstorrent's private PyPI server\\n\\n**What this installs:**\\n- TT-XLA PJRT plugin (JAX hardware integration)\\n- TT-MLIR compiler (bundled with plugin)\\n- TT-Metal runtime libraries (compatible with plugin)\\n- Compatible JAX version\\n\\n[🚀 Install TT-XLA PJRT Plugin](command:tenstorrent.installTtXla)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 2: Test Installation\\n\\n**Quick sanity check:**\\n\\nCreate a test script to verify TT-XLA is working:\\n\\n```python\\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nTest TT-XL\\n\\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/tt-xla-jax.md#L159-L233\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/tt-xla-jax.md#L159-L233\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/audio/whisper-large-v3_galaxy.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 39,\n      \"score\": 0.5358105570077896,\n      \"snippet\": \"# whisper-large-v3 Tenstorrent Support on WH Galaxy\\n\\nSupported weights variants for this model implementation are:\\n\\n- `whisper-large-v3`: [openai/whisper-large-v3](https://huggingface.co/openai/whisper-large-v3) **(default)** \\n- `distil-large-v3`: [distil-whisper/distil-large-v3](https://huggingface.co/distil-whisper/distil-large-v3)\\n\\nTo use non-default weights, replace `whisper-large-v3` in commands below.\\n\\n#### Useful links\\n\\n- [WH Galaxy details](https://tenstorrent.com/hardware/galaxy)\\n- [Search other audio models](./README.md)\\n- [Search other models by model type](../../../README.md#models-by-model-type)\\n\\n`whisper-large-v3` is also supported on hardware:\\n\\n- [WH LoudBox/QuietBox](whisper-\\n\\nSource: ../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/audio/whisper-large-v3_galaxy.md#L1-L39\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/audio/whisper-large-v3_galaxy.md#L1-L39\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/image/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0_t3k.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 37,\n      \"score\": 0.5358105570077896,\n      \"snippet\": \"# stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0 Tenstorrent Support on WH LoudBox/QuietBox\\n\\nSupported weights variants for this model implementation are:\\n\\n- `stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0`: [stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0](https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0) **(default)** \\n- `stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0-img-2-img`: [stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0-img-2-img](https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0-img-2-img)\\n\\nTo use non-default weights, replace `stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0` in commands below.\\n\\n#### Useful links\\n\\n- [WH LoudBox/QuietBox details](https://tenstorrent.com/hardware/tt-loudbox)\\n- [Search other image models](./README.md)\\n- [Sea\\n\\nSource: ../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/image/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0_t3k.md#L1-L37\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/image/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0_t3k.md#L1-L37\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/ct3-configuration-patterns.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 119,\n      \"endLine\": 166,\n      \"score\": 0.49859619140624994,\n      \"snippet\": \"learning_rate: 0.0001            # Standard for fine-tuning\\n  weight_decay: 0.01\\n  use_moreh_adamw: true\\n  use_kahan_summation: false\\n  use_clip_grad_norm: true\\n  clip_grad_norm_max_norm: 1.0\\n  gradient_accumulation_steps: 4   # Effective batch: 8 * 4 = 32\\n  eval_every: 50                   # Validate every 50 steps\\n  model_save_interval: 100         # Checkpoint every 100 steps\\n  tokenizer_type: \\\"bpe\\\"\\n  checkpoint_dir: \\\"checkpoints\\\"\\n  model_config: \\\"model_configs/model.yaml\\\"\\n\\n  # Logging configuration (tt-blacksmith pattern)\\n  log_level: \\\"INFO\\\"\\n  use_wandb: false                 # Optional experiment tracking\\n  wandb_project: \\\"my-training\\\"\\n  wandb_run_name: \\\"n150-experiment\\\"\\n\\n  # Checkpoi\\n\\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/ct3-configuration-patterns.md#L119-L166\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/ct3-configuration-patterns.md#L119-L166\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/ct4-finetuning-basics.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 737,\n      \"endLine\": 793,\n      \"score\": 0.4973596394062042,\n      \"snippet\": \"--model_path ~/tt-metal/tt-train/checkpoints/shakespeare_stage3.pkl_final.pkl \\\\\\n  --max_new_tokens 50 \\\\\\n  --temperature 0.8\\n\\n# Stage 4 (fluent!) - Expect high quality\\npython train_nanogpt.py \\\\\\n  --prompt \\\"ROMEO:\\\" \\\\\\n  --model_path ~/tt-metal/tt-train/checkpoints/shakespeare_final.pkl_final.pkl \\\\\\n  --max_new_tokens 50 \\\\\\n  --temperature 0.8\\n```\\n\\n**This demonstrates hierarchical learning visually!** 🎓\\n\\n---\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 8: Experiment with Temperature & Prompts 🎯\\n\\nNow that you have trained models, explore how temperature affects creativity!\\n\\n### Understanding Temperature\\n\\n**Temperature** controls output creativity:\\n- **0.1** = Very deterministic (greedy-like, repetitive)\\n- **0.5** = Balanced,\\n\\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/ct4-finetuning-basics.md#L737-L793\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/ct4-finetuning-basics.md#L737-L793\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"local\",\n  \"model\": \"hf:ggml-org/embeddinggemma-300m-qat-q8_0-GGUF/embeddinggemma-300m-qat-Q8_0.gguf\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"mode\": \"hybrid\"\n}"}],"details":{"results":[{"path":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md","startLine":1,"endLine":70,"score":0.7810256958007812,"snippet":"---\nid: qb2-life-acceleration\ntitle: \"Game of Life Scaling Demo\"\ndescription: >-\n  Conway's Game of Life at scale. Five progressive demos from 128×128 to 4096×4096 grids (16M cells), demonstrating parallel computation and performance scaling on Tenstorrent hardware.\ncategory: qb2-demos\ntags:\n  - demo\n  - qb2\n  - game-of-life\n  - performance\n  - visualization\n  - cellular-automata\nsupportedHardware:\n  - n150\n  - n300\n  - t3k\n  - p100\n  - p150\n  - p300c\n  - galaxy\nstatus: validated\nvalidatedOn:\n  - p300c\n  - n150\nestimatedMinutes: 10\n---\n\n# Game of Life Scaling Demo\n\n## Overview\n\nFive progressive Conway's Game of Life demonstrations showing performance scaling:\n\n```\nDemo 1: 128×128 grid      (\n\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md#L1-L70","source":"memory","citation":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md#L1-L70"},{"path":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cookbook-game-of-life.md","startLine":399,"endLine":472,"score":0.704022827744484,"snippet":"\"\"\"\n    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 8))\n\n    if title:\n        ax.set_title(title)\n    else:\n        ax.set_title(f\"Generation {generation_num}\")\n\n    ax.imshow(grid, cmap='binary', interpolation='nearest')\n    ax.axis('off')\n    plt.tight_layout()\n    plt.show()\n\ndef compare_patterns(patterns_dict):\n    \"\"\"\n    Display multiple patterns side-by-side.\n\n    Args:\n        patterns_dict: {name: grid} dictionary\n    \"\"\"\n    n = len(patterns_dict)\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, n, figsize=(4*n, 4))\n\n    if n == 1:\n        axes = [axes]\n\n    for ax, (name, grid) in zip(axes, patterns_dict.items()):\n        ax.set_title(name)\n        ax.imshow(grid, cmap='binary', interpolation='nearest\n\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cookbook-game-of-life.md#L399-L472","source":"memory","citation":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cookbook-game-of-life.md#L399-L472"},{"path":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cs-fundamentals-02-memory.md","startLine":177,"endLine":226,"score":0.5653255119919777,"snippet":"│\n\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cs-fundamentals-02-memory.md#L177-L226","source":"memory","citation":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/cs-fundamentals-02-memory.md#L177-L226"},{"path":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-agentic-inference.md","startLine":305,"endLine":372,"score":0.5358105570077896,"snippet":"3. Shows vLLM command for your configuration\n4. Tests connection if server running\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Running the Demo\n\n### Quick Start (Mock)\n\n```bash\ncd ~/tt-scratchpad/qb2-demos/agentic-inference\n\n# Super Demo with mock (no hardware)\n./run_demo.sh 5\n```\n\n### With vLLM (Hardware)\n\n```bash\n# Ensure vLLM running (see setup above)\n./run_demo.sh 5 --llm vllm\n```\n\n### Custom Questions\n\n```bash\n./run_demo.sh 5 --question \"How do transformers enable language understanding?\"\n```\n\n### Advanced Options\n\n```bash\n# Different model\n./run_demo.sh 5 --llm vllm --model ~/models/Qwen3-8B\n\n# Remote vLLM server\n./run_demo.sh 5 --llm vllm --vllm-url http://192.168.1.100:8000/v1\n\n# OpenAI for testing\nexport OPENAI_AP\n\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-agentic-inference.md#L305-L372","source":"memory","citation":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-agentic-inference.md#L305-L372"},{"path":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md","startLine":433,"endLine":518,"score":0.5358105570077896,"snippet":"help='Interactive menu to choose demo')\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    if args.interactive:\n        print(\"\\n🎪 LIFE ACCELERATION DEMO MENU 🎪\\n\")\n        for num, spec in LifeAccelerator.DEMO_SPECS.items():\n            print(f\"  [{num}] {spec['name']}\")\n            print(f\"      Grid: {spec['grid_size'][0]}×{spec['grid_size'][1]}\")\n            print()\n\n        choice = int(input(\"Choose demo (1-5): \"))\n        args.demo = choice\n\n    # Initialize device\n    device = ttnn.open_device(device_id=0)\n\n    try:\n        # Run selected demo\n        accelerator = LifeAccelerator(device, args.demo)\n        accelerator.run()\n    finally:\n        ttnn.close_device(device)\n\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md#L433-L518","source":"memory","citation":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/qb2-life-acceleration.md#L433-L518"},{"path":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/tt-xla-jax.md","startLine":159,"endLine":233,"score":0.5358105570077896,"snippet":"pip install pjrt-plugin-tt --pre --upgrade --extra-index-url https://pypi.eng.aws.tenstorrent.com/\n```\n\n**Flags explained:**\n- `--pre`: Install pre-release (latest features, most tested)\n- `--upgrade`: Ensure latest version\n- `--extra-index-url`: Tenstorrent's private PyPI server\n\n**What this installs:**\n- TT-XLA PJRT plugin (JAX hardware integration)\n- TT-MLIR compiler (bundled with plugin)\n- TT-Metal runtime libraries (compatible with plugin)\n- Compatible JAX version\n\n[🚀 Install TT-XLA PJRT Plugin](command:tenstorrent.installTtXla)\n\n---\n\n## Step 2: Test Installation\n\n**Quick sanity check:**\n\nCreate a test script to verify TT-XLA is working:\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nTest TT-XL\n\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/tt-xla-jax.md#L159-L233","source":"memory","citation":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/tt-xla-jax.md#L159-L233"},{"path":"../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/audio/whisper-large-v3_galaxy.md","startLine":1,"endLine":39,"score":0.5358105570077896,"snippet":"# whisper-large-v3 Tenstorrent Support on WH Galaxy\n\nSupported weights variants for this model implementation are:\n\n- `whisper-large-v3`: [openai/whisper-large-v3](https://huggingface.co/openai/whisper-large-v3) **(default)** \n- `distil-large-v3`: [distil-whisper/distil-large-v3](https://huggingface.co/distil-whisper/distil-large-v3)\n\nTo use non-default weights, replace `whisper-large-v3` in commands below.\n\n#### Useful links\n\n- [WH Galaxy details](https://tenstorrent.com/hardware/galaxy)\n- [Search other audio models](./README.md)\n- [Search other models by model type](../../../README.md#models-by-model-type)\n\n`whisper-large-v3` is also supported on hardware:\n\n- [WH LoudBox/QuietBox](whisper-\n\nSource: ../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/audio/whisper-large-v3_galaxy.md#L1-L39","source":"memory","citation":"../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/audio/whisper-large-v3_galaxy.md#L1-L39"},{"path":"../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/image/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0_t3k.md","startLine":1,"endLine":37,"score":0.5358105570077896,"snippet":"# stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0 Tenstorrent Support on WH LoudBox/QuietBox\n\nSupported weights variants for this model implementation are:\n\n- `stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0`: [stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0](https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0) **(default)** \n- `stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0-img-2-img`: [stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0-img-2-img](https://huggingface.co/stabilityai/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0-img-2-img)\n\nTo use non-default weights, replace `stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0` in commands below.\n\n#### Useful links\n\n- [WH LoudBox/QuietBox details](https://tenstorrent.com/hardware/tt-loudbox)\n- [Search other image models](./README.md)\n- [Sea\n\nSource: ../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/image/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0_t3k.md#L1-L37","source":"memory","citation":"../../../code/tt-inference-server/docs/model_support/image/stable-diffusion-xl-base-1.0_t3k.md#L1-L37"},{"path":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/ct3-configuration-patterns.md","startLine":119,"endLine":166,"score":0.49859619140624994,"snippet":"learning_rate: 0.0001            # Standard for fine-tuning\n  weight_decay: 0.01\n  use_moreh_adamw: true\n  use_kahan_summation: false\n  use_clip_grad_norm: true\n  clip_grad_norm_max_norm: 1.0\n  gradient_accumulation_steps: 4   # Effective batch: 8 * 4 = 32\n  eval_every: 50                   # Validate every 50 steps\n  model_save_interval: 100         # Checkpoint every 100 steps\n  tokenizer_type: \"bpe\"\n  checkpoint_dir: \"checkpoints\"\n  model_config: \"model_configs/model.yaml\"\n\n  # Logging configuration (tt-blacksmith pattern)\n  log_level: \"INFO\"\n  use_wandb: false                 # Optional experiment tracking\n  wandb_project: \"my-training\"\n  wandb_run_name: \"n150-experiment\"\n\n  # Checkpoi\n\nSource: ../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/ct3-configuration-patterns.md#L119-L166","source":"memory","citation":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/ct3-configuration-patterns.md#L119-L166"},{"path":"../../../code/tt-vscode-toolkit/content/lessons/ct4-finetuning-basics.md","startLine":737,"endLine":793,"score":0.4973596394062042,"snippet":"--model_path ~/tt-metal/tt-train/checkpoints/shakespeare_stage3.pkl_final.pkl \\\n  --max_new_tokens 50 \\\n  --temperature 0.8\n\n# Stage 4 (fluent!) - Expect high quality\npython train_nanogpt.py \\\n  --prompt \"ROMEO:\" \\\n  --model_path ~/tt-metal/tt-train/checkpoints/shakespeare_final.pkl_final.pkl \\\n  --max_new_tokens 50 \\\n  --temperature 0.8\n```\n\n**This demonstrates hierarchical learning visually!** 🎓\n\n---\n\n---\n\n## Step 8: Experiment with Temperature & Prompts 🎯\n\nNow that you have trained models, explore how temperature affects creativity!\n\n### Understanding Temperature\n\n**Temperature** controls output creativity:\n- **0.1** = Very deterministic (greedy-li